errors.detail: [SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed: unable to get local issuer certificate (_ssl.c:1020)

remediation: Fix certificate chain/issuer; ensure full intermediate chain is served
Verify host SNI and certificate SANs match the domain

findings.impact: Less discoverable but not a vuln by itself
findings.remediation: Ensure docs exist for developers and protect if sensitive

findings.impact: No 429 observed under bursts; may allow abuse
findings.remediation: Implement rate limiting and anomaly detection

findings.name: Missing HSTS
findings.impact: Users may downgrade to HTTP and be vulnerable to MITM
findings.remediation: Add Strict-Transport-Security with max-age>=15552000; includeSubDomains; preload

findings.name: Missing Permissions-Policy
findings.remediation: Add Permissions-Policy to restrict camera, microphone, geolocation, etc.
